==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|sory}}, from {{inh|en|ang|sāriġ|t=feeling or expressing grief, sorry, grieved, sorrowful, sad, mournful, bitter}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*sairag}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*sairagaz|t=sad}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*sayǝw-|t=hard, rough, painful}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|sairie||sad, grieved}}, {{cog|stq|seerich|t=sore, inflamed}}, {{cog|fy|searich||sad, sorry}}, {{cog|nds|serig||sick, scabby}}, {{cog|de|-}} dialectal {{m|de|sehrig||sore, sad, painful}}, Swedish {{m|sv|sårig}}. More at {{m|en|sore}}.

